1
00:00:09,124 --> 00:00:09,920
<i>C'mon!</i>

2
00:00:16,298 --> 00:00:18,926
<i>Running like a fugitive,</i>

3
00:00:19,968 --> 00:00:22,129
<i>Being chased by something</i>

4
00:00:23,805 --> 00:00:26,467
<i>Inside my heart is pounding</i>

5
00:00:27,576 --> 00:00:30,204
<i>My throat dry like it's withering</i>

6
00:00:31,913 --> 00:00:35,007
<i>For no single one,</i>

7
00:00:35,650 --> 00:00:38,778
<i>To none does belong,</i>

8
00:00:40,255 --> 00:00:44,624
<i>This time is ours, right now...</i>

9
00:00:47,262 --> 00:00:49,025
<i>Unraveling the pain,</i>

10
00:00:49,130 --> 00:00:50,859
<i>Unraveling our hearts,</i>

11
00:00:50,932 --> 00:00:53,264
<i>Unraveling shadows</i>

12
00:00:54,803 --> 00:00:56,566
<i>Stifling our breath,</i>

13
00:00:56,638 --> 00:00:58,538
<i>Reaching for beyond,</i>

14
00:00:58,607 --> 00:01:01,041
<i>Tearing through the dark</i>

15
00:01:02,944 --> 00:01:09,508
<i>In fighting and in love</i>

16
00:01:10,619 --> 00:01:13,110
<i>To the distant light above,</i>

17
00:01:13,888 --> 00:01:16,755
<i>Yes, we are on the way</i>

18
00:01:21,596 --> 00:01:22,893
<i>I wanna rock...</i>

19
00:01:25,367 --> 00:01:26,891
<i>Rockin' my heart</i>

20
00:01:33,752 --> 00:01:34,776
Sorry to keep you waiting.

21
00:01:35,454 --> 00:01:41,620
I'm Ibiki Morino, proctor for
the first test of the Chunin Exam.

22
00:01:46,865 --> 00:01:48,162
You, from Hidden Sound Village!

23
00:01:49,635 --> 00:01:51,865
No doing as you please
before the Exam!

24
00:01:52,771 --> 00:01:54,500
You want to be failed
at the get go?!

25
00:01:56,742 --> 00:02:02,044
Sorry. It's our first time taking the Exams,
so we flipped out... despite ourselves.

26
00:02:03,415 --> 00:02:06,680
Hmph. This is a good opportunity,
so I'll say this.

27
00:02:07,719 --> 00:02:09,414
There will be no battles,
competitions and the like

28
00:02:09,488 --> 00:02:10,978
without the permission
of the proctors!

29
00:02:11,824 --> 00:02:13,587
And even if you get permission,

30
00:02:13,659 --> 00:02:16,890
actions that could lead to the death
of an opponent will not be permitted.

31
00:02:17,729 --> 00:02:21,597
Any pig that screws with me
will be disqualified immediately.

32
00:02:21,900 --> 00:02:22,662
Got it?!

33
00:02:26,305 --> 00:02:29,968
This Exam looks to be easy!

34
00:02:32,744 --> 00:02:36,840
Now then, we will start
the first test of the Chunin Exam!

35
00:02:37,583 --> 00:02:39,016
Turn in your applications,

36
00:02:39,084 --> 00:02:41,552
take one of these number cards
in exchange,

37
00:02:41,687 --> 00:02:43,882
and sit in the seat
matching that number!

38
00:02:44,756 --> 00:02:47,554
After that, we will hand out
the paper for the written test!

39
00:02:47,893 --> 00:02:50,418
Written? Paper?

40
00:02:51,363 --> 00:02:52,523
Paper...

41
00:02:56,001 --> 00:02:59,300
A paper test?!

42
00:02:59,571 --> 00:03:05,339
<i>Start Your Engines.</i>
<i>The Chunin Exam Begins!</i>

43
00:03:16,889 --> 00:03:22,259
<i>Everyone's seats are all scattered...</i>
<i>What should I do?</i>

44
00:03:24,062 --> 00:03:25,689
<i>He's deflated, deflated...</i>

45
00:03:26,031 --> 00:03:28,431
<i>It's the worst type of test for Naruto...</i>

46
00:03:30,536 --> 00:03:31,560
Naruto...

47
00:03:32,738 --> 00:03:36,504
Oh! You are Hinata!
Since when have you?

48
00:03:38,944 --> 00:03:41,879
L-Let's both do our best.

49
00:03:42,314 --> 00:03:43,576
Y-Yeah.

50
00:03:45,017 --> 00:03:46,780
<i>I didn't notice her at all.</i>

51
00:03:47,586 --> 00:03:50,146
<i>Hinata has no presence at all...</i>

52
00:03:51,590 --> 00:03:56,493
There are several important
rules to this first test.

53
00:03:57,963 --> 00:04:02,332
I will take no questions,
so listen well accordingly!

54
00:04:03,101 --> 00:04:05,865
<i>Rules? No questions will be taken...?</i>

55
00:04:06,438 --> 00:04:08,429
First off is the first rule!

56
00:04:09,274 --> 00:04:13,574
You are given ten points
each from the start!

57
00:04:13,879 --> 00:04:16,006
The written test has
ten problems in all!

58
00:04:16,081 --> 00:04:17,639
Each problem is one point.

59
00:04:17,916 --> 00:04:21,113
And, this test is a
point deduction system.

60
00:04:21,787 --> 00:04:24,688
You are deducted one point for
each problem you get wrong!

61
00:04:25,290 --> 00:04:28,657
If you get three wrong,
you'll have seven points!

62
00:04:29,228 --> 00:04:31,822
<i>If I get ten wrong,</i>
<i>I'll have zero points...</i>

63
00:04:32,764 --> 00:04:33,924
The second rule.

64
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:36,124
Pass or failure will be determined

65
00:04:36,201 --> 00:04:38,169
by the total points of
the three person teams.

66
00:04:44,276 --> 00:04:45,937
W-Wait a minute!

67
00:04:46,278 --> 00:04:48,974
What do you mean...
total points of the teams?

68
00:04:49,214 --> 00:04:50,044
Shut up!

69
00:04:50,382 --> 00:04:52,043
There's a perfectly
good reason for this!

70
00:04:52,351 --> 00:04:53,648
Shut up and listen!

71
00:04:54,119 --> 00:04:55,086
<i>Reason...?</i>

72
00:04:55,254 --> 00:04:57,745
If you've got it,
here is the most important next rule!

73
00:04:58,290 --> 00:05:00,315
Those who are deemed by
the sentinels

74
00:05:00,392 --> 00:05:04,829
as having committed an act of
cheating or something similar to that...

75
00:05:05,364 --> 00:05:10,324
will have two points deducted
for each act.

76
00:05:10,702 --> 00:05:11,396
What?

77
00:05:11,703 --> 00:05:12,294
Oh!

78
00:05:12,838 --> 00:05:13,827
In other words...

79
00:05:13,905 --> 00:05:17,397
there may be those who will be
dismissed during this test

80
00:05:17,476 --> 00:05:20,604
without waiting for test grading.

81
00:05:23,915 --> 00:05:25,405
<i>This means they're deducting points</i>

82
00:05:25,484 --> 00:05:27,782
<i>from things other</i>
<i>than the written test problems.</i>

83
00:05:28,086 --> 00:05:30,782
Know that those who
commit awkward cheating...

84
00:05:31,323 --> 00:05:33,416
will bring ruin upon yourselves.

85
00:05:34,026 --> 00:05:36,426
I'll check you anytime.

86
00:05:37,729 --> 00:05:40,323
If you aspire to become
a Chunin at all,

87
00:05:40,399 --> 00:05:44,130
know that Shinobi should act
like exemplary Shinobi.

88
00:05:45,537 --> 00:05:48,404
<i>Relax!</i>
<i>Yes... yes!</i>

89
00:05:48,907 --> 00:05:52,104
<i>Naruto aside,</i>
<i>Sasuke and I are okay!</i>

90
00:05:52,611 --> 00:05:56,206
<i>Even if Naruto gets zero points...</i>
<i>if we cover that...</i>

91
00:05:56,848 --> 00:06:01,217
And, in the case of even one person
on the team getting zero points...

92
00:06:01,653 --> 00:06:04,486
Everyone on that team will fail!

93
00:06:04,790 --> 00:06:05,381
Wha?!

94
00:06:05,457 --> 00:06:06,947
What did he say?!

95
00:06:09,594 --> 00:06:11,118
<i>I feel two menacing stares...</i>

96
00:06:12,197 --> 00:06:13,357
Naruto?

97
00:06:13,799 --> 00:06:17,667
By the way, the last problem will
be given forty five minutes

98
00:06:17,736 --> 00:06:19,067
after the start of the test!

99
00:06:20,305 --> 00:06:21,829
The time for the test is one hour.

100
00:06:25,777 --> 00:06:26,539
Begin!

101
00:06:35,721 --> 00:06:36,710
<i>Could it...</i>

102
00:06:36,788 --> 00:06:39,052
<i>Could it be that,</i>
<i>the fat is really on the fire now...?</i>

103
00:06:39,691 --> 00:06:42,353
<i>Naruto!</i>
<i>Just don't get zero points!</i>

104
00:06:45,430 --> 00:06:49,526
<i>Naruto isn't getting jitters</i>
<i>from the get go, is he...?</i>

105
00:06:50,235 --> 00:06:51,497
<i>This is bad...</i>

106
00:06:55,841 --> 00:06:57,240
<i>As if!</i>

107
00:06:57,309 --> 00:07:01,302
<i>I know I've cleared many obstacles</i>
<i>like this before...</i>

108
00:07:01,513 --> 00:07:03,640
<i>At times like this, one should</i>
<i>look at all the problems</i>

109
00:07:03,715 --> 00:07:05,239
<i>without feeling pressed</i>
<i>or making a fuss!</i>

110
00:07:05,317 --> 00:07:06,909
<i>And then with utmost effort</i>

111
00:07:06,985 --> 00:07:09,681
<i>I should tackle the problems that look</i>
<i>easy to understand!</i>

112
00:07:10,355 --> 00:07:13,984
<i>Let's see, the first problem...</i>
<i>is a code text, eh...</i>

113
00:07:14,159 --> 00:07:16,093
<i>Excellent, I say!</i>

114
00:07:18,730 --> 00:07:19,628
<i>Next! Next!</i>

115
00:07:19,698 --> 00:07:21,666
<i>Let's see... the second problem...</i>

116
00:07:22,401 --> 00:07:26,428
<i>The parabola B in the diagram illustrates</i>
<i>the greatest possible distance</i>

117
00:07:26,505 --> 00:07:31,169
<i>Enemy Ninja A can throw his Shuriken</i>
<i>from a tree seven meters high...</i>

118
00:07:32,644 --> 00:07:35,112
<i>Predict and answer the Enemy Ninja's</i>
<i>character inferred</i>

119
00:07:35,180 --> 00:07:37,648
<i>from the ellipse this Shuriken forms,</i>

120
00:07:37,716 --> 00:07:41,550
<i>also answer the longest firing range</i>
<i>in battle on flat ground</i>

121
00:07:41,620 --> 00:07:43,645
<i>and explain your basis.</i>

122
00:07:45,290 --> 00:07:49,056
<i>T-This is an... integrated problem based</i>
<i>on predictions</i>

123
00:07:49,127 --> 00:07:53,223
<i>of uncertain conditions and</i>
<i>dynamic energy analysis application!</i>

124
00:07:54,232 --> 00:07:56,632
<i>There's no way</i>
<i>Naruto can solve this!</i>

125
00:07:56,701 --> 00:07:57,690
<i>I mean...</i>

126
00:07:57,769 --> 00:08:02,001
<i>hardly anyone except me</i>
<i>can solve this problem!</i>

127
00:08:04,810 --> 00:08:06,141
<i>Okay, next!</i>
<i>Next!</i>

128
00:08:11,316 --> 00:08:13,750
<i>These other problems...</i>
<i>are nothing but difficult ones.</i>

129
00:08:23,195 --> 00:08:24,321
<i>I see...</i>

130
00:08:25,597 --> 00:08:28,532
<i>I don't... understand even</i>
<i>one of these problems.</i>

131
00:08:32,637 --> 00:08:34,366
<i>Oh, no, this is bad!</i>

132
00:08:34,539 --> 00:08:36,029
<i>For real! For real!</i>

133
00:08:36,107 --> 00:08:39,304
<i>What should I do?</i>
<i>What should I do? What should I do?</i>

134
00:08:48,553 --> 00:08:52,819
<i>If about ten of all fifty one teams</i>
<i>are able to pass,</i>

135
00:08:53,458 --> 00:08:56,154
<i>it will be bad if I didn't stretch myself and</i>
<i>get a considerable amount of points.</i>

136
00:08:57,329 --> 00:08:59,820
<i>It's like a system inviting cheating...</i>

137
00:09:00,732 --> 00:09:04,133
<i>I hope Sasuke and Naruto</i>
<i>won't panic and cheat.</i>

138
00:09:06,638 --> 00:09:09,607
<i>It's okay...</i>
<i>Naruto's not that much of an idiot...</i>

139
00:09:10,342 --> 00:09:11,468
<i>I know that...</i>

140
00:09:15,080 --> 00:09:15,978
<i>Don't panic...</i>

141
00:09:16,047 --> 00:09:19,107
<i>For now, all there is to do is to be</i>
<i>very, very cautious...</i>

142
00:09:19,184 --> 00:09:22,312
<i>and cheat without being found out!</i>

143
00:09:26,791 --> 00:09:28,952
<i>No! No! I can't, that's no good,</i>
<i>no good!</i>

144
00:09:29,027 --> 00:09:31,222
<i>I can't tread on such thin ice!</i>

145
00:09:33,098 --> 00:09:35,259
<i>At any rate, this elaborate fuss...</i>

146
00:09:35,667 --> 00:09:39,159
<i>It's like a trick assuming</i>
<i>that we're going to cheat.</i>

147
00:09:40,472 --> 00:09:42,770
<i>They probably check with that paper...</i>

148
00:09:45,977 --> 00:09:47,342
<i>Somebody got nailed.</i>

149
00:09:48,346 --> 00:09:51,076
<i>Cheating deducts two points.</i>

150
00:09:52,617 --> 00:09:53,982
<i>Two point deduction, huh...</i>

151
00:09:55,854 --> 00:09:59,221
<i>Ordinarily, it'd be failure the moment</i>
<i>the cheating was discovered...</i>

152
00:10:07,132 --> 00:10:10,363
<i>Know that those who</i>
<i>commit awkward cheating</i>

153
00:10:10,435 --> 00:10:12,903
<i>will bring ruin upon themselves.</i>

154
00:10:13,438 --> 00:10:17,101
<i>Shinobi should act like exemplary Shinobi.</i>

155
00:10:18,410 --> 00:10:20,378
<i>I see, so that's how it is, eh.</i>

156
00:10:21,212 --> 00:10:23,737
<i>This wasn't just an achievement test!</i>

157
00:10:23,915 --> 00:10:25,644
<i>The real aim was...</i>

158
00:10:26,851 --> 00:10:29,319
<i>a test to see the ability</i>
<i>for intensive information collection</i>

159
00:10:29,588 --> 00:10:32,318
<i>with the full use of deception</i>
<i>and concealment techniques.</i>

160
00:10:35,827 --> 00:10:37,988
<i>"Shinobi should read</i>
<i>the double bluff, " eh...</i>

161
00:10:38,797 --> 00:10:40,765
<i>In other words, the true intention</i>
<i>of the proctor is...</i>

162
00:10:41,132 --> 00:10:44,158
<i>if you're going to cheat,</i>
<i>not "awkward cheating,"</i>

163
00:10:44,769 --> 00:10:48,705
<i>but "like exemplary Shinobi",</i>
<i>don't get caught.</i>

164
00:10:49,708 --> 00:10:52,905
<i>Viewed in this light, the extraordinariness</i>
<i>of the point deduction system,</i>

165
00:10:52,978 --> 00:10:58,610
<i>the lenience of only deducting two points</i>
<i>for each discovery of cheating makes sense.</i>

166
00:10:59,751 --> 00:11:00,979
<i>In other words,</i>

167
00:11:01,052 --> 00:11:04,215
<i>what's being tested here is how</i>
<i>we can gather the correct answers</i>

168
00:11:04,289 --> 00:11:07,986
<i>without having our cheating detected</i>
<i>by the proctors or</i>

169
00:11:08,059 --> 00:11:10,994
<i>by the one being cheated on.</i>

170
00:11:11,830 --> 00:11:13,525
<i>Realize it quick, Naruto!</i>

171
00:11:14,666 --> 00:11:15,826
<i>It'll turn into a fatal mistake!</i>

172
00:11:16,601 --> 00:11:17,499
<i>Realize it!</i>

173
00:11:24,409 --> 00:11:26,104
<i>This is bad. Believe it...</i>

174
00:11:28,381 --> 00:11:33,409
<i>If the purpose of this test is seeing</i>
<i>the ability to gather information...</i>

175
00:11:35,121 --> 00:11:38,386
<i>then there should be someone</i>
<i>in this classroom somewhere...</i>

176
00:11:39,091 --> 00:11:41,184
<i>who knows the answers</i>
<i>to the problems!</i>

177
00:11:46,966 --> 00:11:48,490
<i>So Gaara has also started, eh...</i>

178
00:11:49,535 --> 00:11:52,129
<i>Hmph... l'm counting on you, Crow.</i>

179
00:12:05,651 --> 00:12:11,749
Yahoo, good boy, Akamaru!
Next is problem four!

180
00:12:23,135 --> 00:12:24,397
<i>Judging from this rhythm...</i>

181
00:12:24,470 --> 00:12:27,303
<i>The stroke order...</i>
<i>and the number of strokes...</i>

182
00:12:29,275 --> 00:12:30,674
<i>I see.</i>

183
00:12:47,093 --> 00:12:48,651
<i>Okay! Please tell me.</i>

184
00:12:54,100 --> 00:12:54,930
<i>Eight, huh.</i>

185
00:13:06,345 --> 00:13:08,210
<i>Lee, if you can see it,</i>
<i>wear your headband!</i>

186
00:13:29,101 --> 00:13:31,467
<i>Time is rapidly going by!</i>

187
00:13:31,537 --> 00:13:34,836
<i>Oh, man! I'm afraid all there</i>
<i>is to do is cheat...</i>

188
00:13:35,641 --> 00:13:37,438
<i>But, if I'm discovered,</i>

189
00:13:37,577 --> 00:13:40,546
<i>it'll be trouble for Sakura</i>
<i>and Sasuke.</i>

190
00:13:41,847 --> 00:13:43,781
<i>On the other hand,</i>
<i>if I get zero points...</i>

191
00:13:43,849 --> 00:13:46,841
<i>Sakura and Sasuke will be</i>
<i>my companions in failure.</i>

192
00:13:47,987 --> 00:13:48,783
Naruto...

193
00:13:51,324 --> 00:13:55,522
I'll show you... my test.

194
00:13:55,895 --> 00:13:56,623
<i>Huh...?</i>

195
00:13:57,530 --> 00:13:59,657
<i>What is Hinata saying...?</i>

196
00:14:01,300 --> 00:14:03,427
<i>W-Why would she do</i>
<i>such a thing for me?</i>

197
00:14:05,371 --> 00:14:08,898
<i>Could it be... some kind of trickery?</i>

198
00:14:11,577 --> 00:14:14,603
<i>But Hinata is not one to do</i>
<i>something like that...</i>

199
00:14:16,282 --> 00:14:20,116
<i>No... But she might've been coaxed into</i>
<i>attempting to trap me by Kiba and others...</i>

200
00:14:21,153 --> 00:14:23,417
Hinata, let me ask you one thing!

201
00:14:23,856 --> 00:14:24,515
Huh?!

202
00:14:24,690 --> 00:14:26,681
Why would you show me?

203
00:14:31,063 --> 00:14:32,928
Uh... uh... actually...

204
00:14:35,668 --> 00:14:38,000
I... I...

205
00:14:43,275 --> 00:14:47,712
I don't want you, Naruto...
to leave at this stage...

206
00:14:52,885 --> 00:14:56,082
Y-You see...
the nine of us are the only rookies...

207
00:14:56,589 --> 00:14:59,854
and I have many anxieties about
what's to come, so!

208
00:15:02,194 --> 00:15:07,029
I get it now! I was kind of
strangely suspicious of you!

209
00:15:10,002 --> 00:15:13,563
<i>Anyhow! This is crazy lucky, I say!</i>

210
00:15:13,839 --> 00:15:15,670
<i>Thank goodness I'm next to Hinata...</i>

211
00:15:27,453 --> 00:15:30,820
<i>W-What was that?</i>
<i>I was about to turn...</i>

212
00:15:35,227 --> 00:15:36,455
W-What was that for, sir?!

213
00:15:37,063 --> 00:15:40,624
You made five mistakes. You fail!

214
00:15:41,133 --> 00:15:42,657
N-No way...

215
00:15:43,169 --> 00:15:47,265
His two buddies, both of you get out
of the classroom, right now.

216
00:16:00,219 --> 00:16:01,948
#23 fails!

217
00:16:02,421 --> 00:16:04,412
#43 and #27 fail!

218
00:16:04,590 --> 00:16:05,921
Noooo!

219
00:16:08,360 --> 00:16:13,662
Hey, hey! Do you have proof that
I cheated five whole times?!

220
00:16:13,899 --> 00:16:18,131
Really, are you guys properly checking
this number of people?

221
00:16:21,407 --> 00:16:22,396
Listen up...

222
00:16:22,475 --> 00:16:27,936
Even among us Chunin, we're elite
who were selected for this Exam.

223
00:16:28,881 --> 00:16:32,044
We don't overlook you blinking once...

224
00:16:32,485 --> 00:16:35,613
In a matter of speaking,
this strength is the proof.

225
00:16:40,526 --> 00:16:41,515
Naruto?

226
00:16:43,796 --> 00:16:45,354
Hurry... Look...

227
00:17:04,784 --> 00:17:08,584
Hinata... You don't get it, do you?

228
00:17:09,054 --> 00:17:09,713
What?

229
00:17:10,623 --> 00:17:14,855
An awesome ninja like me
won't cheat. Believe it!

230
00:17:15,761 --> 00:17:17,422
N-Naruto.

231
00:17:18,230 --> 00:17:19,629
B-But...

232
00:17:23,969 --> 00:17:25,698
Also, if something went wrong,

233
00:17:25,771 --> 00:17:29,571
you'd be in a hot spot for
helping me cheat, right?!

234
00:17:29,909 --> 00:17:30,671
What?!

235
00:17:30,943 --> 00:17:32,001
<i>Naruto...</i>

236
00:17:36,081 --> 00:17:39,744
I'm... sorry...
I-I did something uncalled for...

237
00:17:41,086 --> 00:17:43,077
Nah, it's okay.

238
00:17:44,723 --> 00:17:47,123
<i>I... went and acted big.</i>

239
00:17:47,827 --> 00:17:51,524
<i>What should I do?</i>
<i>I'm extremely stupid.</i>

240
00:17:57,069 --> 00:17:58,161
<i>Byakugan!</i>

241
00:18:00,973 --> 00:18:02,201
<i>Sharingan!</i>

242
00:18:02,508 --> 00:18:04,635
<i>I'll copy all his movements!</i>

243
00:18:07,346 --> 00:18:09,371
<i>My hand is moving fluently...</i>

244
00:18:09,949 --> 00:18:11,678
<i>I hit the jackpot straight away</i>
<i>with this guy.</i>

245
00:18:15,321 --> 00:18:17,551
<i>Sakura, it looks like you're done, eh.</i>

246
00:18:17,990 --> 00:18:20,322
<i>I'm acknowledging that your smarts</i>

247
00:18:20,392 --> 00:18:23,259
<i>and the width of your forehead</i>
<i>are exceptional.</i>

248
00:18:23,863 --> 00:18:26,058
<i>So you should thank me.</i>

249
00:18:26,432 --> 00:18:28,923
<i>Thank me for getting to be</i>
<i>the target for this Jutsu.</i>

250
00:18:29,301 --> 00:18:31,132
<i>Ninja Art, Mind Transfer Jutsu!</i>

251
00:18:38,577 --> 00:18:42,240
<i>So Ino... started using that Jutsu...</i>

252
00:18:43,048 --> 00:18:46,176
<i>There's no countering that spell of Ino's...</i>

253
00:18:50,322 --> 00:18:55,259
<i>Sakura, I let myself move</i>
<i>into your mind for just a little bit.</i>

254
00:18:56,128 --> 00:18:58,358
<i>I have to memorize the answers quick.</i>

255
00:18:58,530 --> 00:19:01,226
<i>I've got to pass these answers</i>
<i>to Shikamaru and Choji.</i>

256
00:19:02,401 --> 00:19:04,062
#59! Fails!

257
00:19:05,037 --> 00:19:06,527
#33! #9!

258
00:19:07,873 --> 00:19:09,807
<i>This is the thirteenth group to fail.</i>

259
00:19:11,677 --> 00:19:13,235
#41 fails.

260
00:19:13,679 --> 00:19:16,375
#35, #62 fails!

261
00:19:16,649 --> 00:19:17,581
No way!

262
00:19:21,287 --> 00:19:22,276
<i>That brat...</i>

263
00:19:23,122 --> 00:19:27,923
<i>He coolly proceeds through this</i>
<i>ruckus without moving an eyelash.</i>

264
00:19:29,395 --> 00:19:31,260
<i>Very well done considering he's new.</i>

265
00:19:43,776 --> 00:19:46,108
<i>The optic nerves are connected...</i>

266
00:19:46,679 --> 00:19:48,977
<i>The third eye... open!</i>

267
00:20:05,164 --> 00:20:06,688
<i>Ugh! There's dirt in my eye...</i>

268
00:20:07,566 --> 00:20:08,555
<i>Dang it!</i>

269
00:20:25,584 --> 00:20:26,516
Excuse me.

270
00:20:26,986 --> 00:20:27,782
What is it?

271
00:20:28,354 --> 00:20:29,981
I need to go to the bathroom...

272
00:20:31,991 --> 00:20:34,619
We will accompany you
to the bathroom.

273
00:20:35,494 --> 00:20:36,722
I see...

274
00:20:42,601 --> 00:20:47,436
Anyhow... the proctors are
nothing so special!

275
00:20:48,340 --> 00:20:51,468
They don't realize that the proctors
have increased by one...

276
00:20:52,011 --> 00:20:54,036
Eh, don't you think so...

277
00:20:54,613 --> 00:20:55,841
Crow?

278
00:21:00,919 --> 00:21:03,683
<i>Forty minutes have passed</i>
<i>since the test started...</i>

279
00:21:04,189 --> 00:21:05,850
<i>Twenty minutes left... huh...</i>

280
00:21:07,259 --> 00:21:08,658
<i>Since it's come to this,</i>

281
00:21:08,727 --> 00:21:12,663
<i>it's the last problem to be given</i>
<i>forty five minutes after the start of the test.</i>

282
00:21:15,200 --> 00:21:17,725
<i>All there is to do is bet on this.</i>
<i>Believe it!</i>

283
00:22:50,965 --> 00:22:52,990
Even if I take it, I'm a Genin for life
once I get it wrong?!

284
00:22:53,067 --> 00:22:54,534
<i>Really? Really? Really?</i>

285
00:22:54,602 --> 00:22:56,593
If I don't take it, I'll fail with
my comrades immediately?

286
00:22:56,670 --> 00:22:58,297
<i>No way, no way, no way.</i>

287
00:22:58,372 --> 00:23:00,340
The hopeless rule for problem ten!

288
00:23:00,407 --> 00:23:02,068
<i>Not good, not good, not good.</i>

289
00:23:02,143 --> 00:23:04,407
No way can I choose which one!

290
00:23:04,478 --> 00:23:06,207
<i>What to do, do, do, do.</i>

291
00:23:06,280 --> 00:23:08,748
This is seriously, seriously bad!

292
00:23:08,816 --> 00:23:11,182
<i>Bad, bad, bad, bad.</i>

293
00:23:11,452 --> 00:23:15,047
Next episode:
"The Tenth Question: All or Nothing!"
